<p>Where do you like to work?</p>

<h2 id="the-evening-lift">The evening lift</h2>
<p>Working all day and I tired myself out. I can now focus.</p>

<h2 id="make-reading-easier">Make reading easier</h2>
<p>Zotero and Papership. Pay for the upgrades. Now is not the time to cheap out.</p>

<h2 id="make-starting-easier">Make starting easier</h2>
<p>Have your computer open up your key programs right at boot up.</p>

<h2 id="file-backup-and-redundancy">File backup and redundancy</h2>
<p>Set up a backup plan
Backup and redundancy
Use Git
It’s kind of fun to check in major versions of a chapter. I pay $4 for storage.</p>

<h2 id="what-is-your-reward-system">What is your reward system?</h2>

<h2 id="dreamsidealsreality-where-is-the-disconnect">Dreams/Ideals/reality: Where is the disconnect?</h2>
<p>All throughout my time in grad school, I had this dream that I would ride my bike to a park or a beach. I would leave at a civilized time in the morning, around 8 am or so, and read for a few hours, grab a coffee on the way home, and really delight in this process. I did that a few times, certainly less than 10. But every year this dream would resurface – especially at the end of Spring quarter. I’d always say, “maybe this is the year”. Again, I did that, but not really. I had this dream that I would do that twice a week. Tuesdays and Thursdays. But I never did that. So, what was the hold up?
Papers and books are heavy.
Parks are dirty and windy.
But maybe I didn’t want that?</p>

